Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 15:52:51 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] rapier - 1.8 combat: restore 1.8 armor reduction formula
 (flat 4% per point)

replaces the 1.9+ toughness-scaled formula:
  f = 2 + toughness/4; effective = clamp(armor - damage/f, armor*0.2, 20)
  reduction = effective/25

with the 1.8.9 flat formula:
  reduction = clamp(armor * 0.04, 0, 0.8)

consequences: armor is never bypassed by high-damage weapons and
toughness (netherite) has no effect (post-1.8 stat). cap stays at 80%.

diff --git a/net/minecraft/world/damagesource/CombatRules.java b/net/minecraft/world/damagesource/CombatRules.java
index 5f8637dfe4703cb78f486fe49d2e81518cf48715..dbea47f8a9f7852a9227482469b728434ca7aee4 100644
--- a/net/minecraft/world/damagesource/CombatRules.java
+++ b/net/minecraft/world/damagesource/CombatRules.java
@@ -14,9 +14,8 @@ public class CombatRules {
     private static final int NUM_ARMOR_ITEMS = 4;
 
     public static float getDamageAfterAbsorb(LivingEntity entity, float damageAmount, DamageSource damageSource, float armorValue, float armorToughness) {
-        float f = 2.0F + armorToughness / 4.0F;
-        float f1 = Mth.clamp(armorValue - damageAmount / f, armorValue * 0.2F, 20.0F);
-        float f2 = f1 / 25.0F;
+        // rapier - 1.8 combat: flat 4% reduction per armor point (cap at 80%), drop toughness scaling and high-damage bypass
+        float f2 = Mth.clamp(armorValue * 0.04F, 0.0F, 0.8F);
         ItemStack weaponItem = damageSource.getWeaponItem();
         float f3;
         if (weaponItem != null && entity.level() instanceof ServerLevel serverLevel) {
